                    .instructions
                        h1 Features 
                        ul 
                            li Add EBOM items to the MBOM easily with clicks
                            li Add further items to the MBOM using drag &amp; drop 
                            li Use the Disassemble mode to quickly define the MBOM by reversing the order
                            li Use color codes to identify mismatches in EBOM and MBOM 
                            li Access details of selected items in right hand side panel whenever needed
                            li Manage multiple MBOMs per EBOM item (i.e. site specific BOMs)
                        h1 Important
                        p This editor helps users in copying &amp; extending one BOM into another. Depending on the tenant configuration, this may involve a single items workspaces or multiple ones. For example, you may want to copy a Vault Items and BOMs structure into an Items and BOMs structure to have different access permission controls and business logic. However, you may also want to manage both BOMs in the same workspace, for example the Items or Vault Items and BOMs. While the editor supports both scenarios, the setup is slightly different in each scenario.
                        p Note that the viewer inside the MBOM Editor will only work if the base EBOM item has a dwf file attached.
                        p The installation instructions shown below will refer to the source BOM as 'EBOM' and to the target BOM as 'MBOM'. Most probably, you will use the Items (and BOMs) workspace to manage both the EBOM and MBOM. In this case, a minimum of adjustments is needed. This documentation will focus on this primary use case but also explain the extra configurations required when using two workspaces instead.
                        h1 Configuration Changes for EBOM Workspace (Items)
                        h2 Extend Item Details
