                            li 3D viewer helps to identify the right items
                            li Keep multiple BOM structures in sync
                            li Manage multiple variants at the same time or focus a single variant only
                            li Dynamically define the properties that define a variant
                        h1 New Workspace Item Variants 
                        p A new workspace is required to manage items and BOMs that are specific for a given variant. These item variant will refere to a base item to allow for data reuse by using derived fields, but will also have additional fields that define a variant (i.e. color, material etc.)
                        h2 Create new workspace
                        p Use the 
                            strong Workspace Manager 
                            |to create new workspace 
                            strong Item Variants 
                            |. 
                            img.border(src='images/apps/variant-manager-1.png' style='max-width:1092px;')
                        h2 Set Item Details of new workspace
                        p Create 3 sections in 
                            strong Item Details 
                            | tab: 
                        ul
                            li  Basic
                            li Variant Definition
                            li Base Item 
                        p Add the following fields to section 
                            strong Basic
                            |:
                            ol  
                                li Number (id: NUMBER, Single Line Text, length : 20, read-only)
                                li Title (id: TITLE, Single Line Text, length: 200, editable)
                                li Base Item (id: BASE_ITEM, Picklist to [WS] Items, single selection, read-only)
                                li DMS_ID_BASE_ITEM (id: DMS_ID_BASE_ITEM, Single Line Text, length : 20, hidden, editable)
                                li NAME (id:NAME, Single Line Text, hidden, ready-only)
                                    br
                                    | Set a computation formula for the NAME field: 
                                    p.code CASE WHEN(TITLE is null) Then NUMBER Else TITLE END
                        p In section 
                            strong Variant Definition
                            |, add all the fields that will be used to define a variant. For example: Color and Material. This may include any type of field, including pick lists.
                        p All data that should be derived from the 
                            strong Base Item 
                            | should be defined in section 
                            strong Base Item Data
                            |. Make use of derived fields to copy data from the given base item. This may include the Type, Description, Image and further fields of your items workspace.
                        img.border(src='images/apps/variant-manager-4.png' style='max-width:728px;')
